= Weekly Meal Prep System

This system is designed around:

- ~700–800 calorie meals
- high protein
- high fiber
- freezer-friendly prep
- minimal weekday cooking
- reusable components
- minimal ingredient sprawl

Daily structure:

- 1 lunch meal
- 1 dinner meal
- optional fruit and mozzarella sticks for additional hunger

== Weekly Component Prep

=== Component 1 — Homemade Paneer

Makes approximately 12 portions.

=== Ingredients

- 3 gallons whole milk
- 180g lemon juice or white vinegar
- 10g salt

==== Method

+ Heat milk to 90C.
+ Stir occasionally to prevent scorching.
+ Remove from heat.
+ Slowly add lemon juice or vinegar while stirring gently.
+ Rest 10 minutes.
+ Strain through cheesecloth.
+ Rinse lightly with cold water.
+ Press under weight for 60–90 minutes.
+ Refrigerate fully.
+ Cube paneer.

==== Portioning

- 12 containers of 130–135g paneer

Freeze most portions.

=== Component 2 — Challah

==== Ingredients

- 180g warm water
- 50g sugar
- 7g active dry yeast
- 480–540g all-purpose flour
- 80g vegetable oil
- 2 eggs
- 1 egg yolk
- 6g salt

Optional:

- sesame seeds
- poppy seeds

==== Method

+ Combine warm water, sugar, and yeast.
+ Rest 5 minutes until foamy.
+ Add flour, oil, eggs, egg yolk, and salt.
+ Knead 8–10 minutes.
+ Rise 1–2 hours.
+ Divide into 6 strands.
+ Braid loaf.
+ Rise 30–60 minutes.
+ Brush with egg white.
+ Bake at 175C for 20–25 minutes.

==== Portioning

- 12 slices of 75g

Freeze individually.

=== Component 3 — Roasted Vegetable Mix

==== Ingredients

- 1000g mushrooms
- 700g onion
- 700g bell pepper
- 40g olive oil
- 10g salt
- 6g black pepper
- 5g smoked paprika
- 4g garlic powder
- 3g cumin

==== Method

+ Slice vegetables.
+ Toss with olive oil and salt.
+ Roast at 220C for 30–35 minutes.
+ Stir halfway through.
+ Cool completely.

==== Portioning

- 12 containers of 185–190g

Freeze.

=== Component 4 — Spinach Base

==== Ingredients

- 1600g frozen spinach
- 25g garlic
- 15g olive oil
- 8g salt
- 5g cumin
- 4g coriander
- 3g turmeric
- 2g fenugreek leaves (kasuri methi)
- 2g chili flakes

==== Method

+ Heat olive oil.
+ Cook garlic 1 minute.
+ Add spinach.
+ Cook until excess moisture evaporates.

==== Portioning

- 12 containers of 120g

Freeze.

=== Component 5 — Pinto Beans

==== Ingredients

- 3 cans pinto beans (15.5 oz / 439g each)
- 5g cumin
- 4g chili powder
- 3g smoked paprika
- 2g garlic powder
- salt to taste

==== Method

+ Drain.
+ Rinse thoroughly.
+ Portion.

==== Portioning

- 8 containers of 90g drained beans

Freeze.

=== Component 6 — Chickpeas

==== Ingredients

- 3 cans chickpeas (15.5 oz / 439g each)

==== Method

+ Drain.
+ Rinse thoroughly.
+ Portion.

==== Portioning

- 8 containers of 90g drained chickpeas

Freeze.

=== Component 7 — Hummus

==== Ingredients

- 1 can chickpeas (15.5 oz / 439g each)
- 25g sesame seeds
- 40g lemon juice
- 15g olive oil
- 10g garlic
- 6g salt
- 3g cumin
- 60–120g cold water

==== Method

+ Toast sesame seeds lightly.
+ Add sesame seeds to blender.
+ Blend until mostly smooth.
+ Add chickpeas, lemon juice, garlic, salt, and olive oil.
+ Blend while gradually adding cold water.
+ Blend until smooth and creamy.

==== Portioning

- 6 containers of 70–75g

Refrigerate or freeze.

=== Component 8 — Pizza Dough Balls

==== Ingredients

- 630g bread flour
- 15g sugar
- 10g kosher salt
- 10g instant yeast
- 32g olive oil
- 420g lukewarm water

==== Method

+ Combine dry ingredients.
+ Add water and olive oil.
+ Knead until smooth and elastic.
+ Divide into 8 dough balls.
+ Cold ferment 1–5 days.

==== Portioning

- 8 dough balls of approximately 140g each

Freeze after at least 24 hours of fermentation if desired.


== Approximate Component Nutrition

Per prepared portion:

- Paneer portion (130–135g): ~430 calories, ~26g protein
- Challah slice (75g): ~240 calories, ~7g protein
- Roasted vegetable portion: ~60 calories, ~3g protein
- Spinach portion: ~35 calories, ~4g protein
- Pinto bean portion: ~105 calories, ~7g protein
- Chickpea portion: ~110 calories, ~5g protein
- Hummus portion: ~110 calories, ~4g protein
- Pizza dough ball: ~345 calories, ~10g protein

=== Pizza Equipment Recommendation

Ideal size:

- 23–25cm pizza
- 9–10 inch pizza

Best surfaces:

+ Pizza steel
+ Cast iron pan
+ Pizza stone

== Meal Recipes

=== Meal 1 — Challah Lunch Plate

==== Components

- 1 challah portion
- 1 paneer portion
- 1 roasted vegetable portion
- 1 spinach portion
- 1/2 hummus portion

==== Additional Ingredients

- 20g balsamic vinegar
- black pepper
- flaky salt

==== Method

+ Reheat roasted vegetables and spinach.
+ Add balsamic vinegar.
+ Warm challah.
+ Plate with paneer and hummus.

==== Approximate Nutrition

- ~760 calories
- ~44g protein
- ~15g fiber

=== Meal 2 — Palak Paneer Plate

==== Components

- 1 paneer portion
- 2 spinach portions
- 1 challah portion

==== Additional Ingredients

- 80g Greek yogurt
- 2g fenugreek leaves (kasuri methi)
- cumin
- garam masala
- black pepper

==== Method

+ Reheat spinach portions.
+ Stir in Greek yogurt.
+ Add paneer.
+ Serve with challah.

==== Approximate Nutrition

- ~740 calories
- ~42g protein
- ~16g fiber

=== Meal 3 — Paneer Piccata Pasta

==== Components

- 1 paneer portion
- 1 roasted vegetable portion
- 1 spinach portion

==== Additional Ingredients

- 70g dry pasta
- 15g lemon juice
- 10g capers
- black pepper
- oregano
- chili flakes

==== Method

- Cook pasta.
- Reheat roasted vegetables and spinach.
- Add lemon juice and capers.
- Toss with pasta and paneer.

==== Approximate Nutrition

- ~760 calories
- ~43g protein
- ~14g fiber

=== Meal 4 — Greek Salad Plate

==== Components

- 1 paneer portion
- 1 chickpea portion
- 1/2 hummus portion
- 1 challah portion

==== Additional Ingredients

- 200g cucumber
- 150g tomato
- 5g olive oil
- 20g lemon juice
- 20g balsamic vinegar
- oregano
- salt
- pepper

==== Method

+ Chop cucumber and tomato.
+ Combine with chickpeas.
+ Add paneer.
+ Dress with olive oil, lemon juice, balsamic vinegar, oregano, salt, and pepper.
+ Serve with hummus and challah.

==== Approximate Nutrition

- ~790 calories
- ~42g protein
- ~18g fiber

=== Meal 5 — Personal Pizza

==== Components

- 1 pizza dough ball
- 1 roasted vegetable portion
- 1/2 paneer portion

==== Additional Ingredients

- 90g tomato sauce
- 40g mozzarella

==== Method

+ Stretch dough into a 23–25cm round.
+ Add tomato sauce.
+ Add mozzarella.
+ Add paneer and roasted vegetables.
+ Bake at maximum oven temperature.

==== Approximate Nutrition

- ~730 calories
- ~36g protein
- ~10g fiber

=== Meal 6 — Pinto Bean Torta

==== Components

- 1 pinto bean portion
- 1 roasted vegetable portion
- 1/2 paneer portion

==== Additional Ingredients

- 1 challah slice
- 200g egg whites
- 60g Greek yogurt
- cumin
- chili powder
- smoked paprika
- hot sauce or salsa

==== Method

- Cook egg whites.
- Reheat beans and vegetables.
- Crisp paneer.
- Toast challah lightly.
- Assemble sandwich/torta.

==== Approximate Nutrition

- ~710 calories
- ~49g protein
- ~15g fiber

=== Meal 7 — Pasta Salad

==== Components

- 1 pinto bean portion
- 1 roasted vegetable portion
- 1 spinach portion
- 1 paneer portion

==== Additional Ingredients

- 70g dry pasta
- 10g olive oil
- 15g balsamic vinegar

==== Method

- Cook pasta.
- Combine all ingredients.
- Toss thoroughly.
- Serve warm or cold.

==== Approximate Nutrition

- ~780 calories
- ~42g protein
- ~17g fiber

